[2
Date: Thu, 29 Jun 2000 17:14:30 CDT
From: Andrea Guajardo <andi131@hotmail.com>
Source: News reports [edited

News reports on 29 Jun 2000 state that a possible case of Hantavirus
Pulmonary Syndrome may have been detected in an elementary school employee
in the Houston suburb of Missouri City, Texas. The employee was said to
have been cleaning out a storage closet and became ill some time later.
Laboratory results are pending to confirm the presence of [a hantavirus.
The reports state that no [illnesses due to a hantavirus infection have
ever been confirmed in Harris County [Houston. In fact, only 15 cases
have ever been confirmed in Texas, the majority of them in the western
regions of state.
